<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc9e7ddd2-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s485h–3"><num value="485h–3">§ 485h–3.</num><heading> “Long-term contract” defined</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">As used in sections 485h–1 to 485h–5 of this title, the term “long-term contract” shall mean any contract the term of which is more than ten years.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idc9e7ddd3-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598">(<ref href="/us/act/1956-07-02/ch492/s3">July 2, 1956, ch. 492, § 3</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/70/484">70 Stat. 484</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idc9e7ddd4-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idc9e7ddd5-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="idc9e7ddd6-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section was not enacted as part of the Reclamation Project Act of 1939 which comprises this subchapter.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
